Skipped `e65855a52b47` (uclamp deadlock). The bug requires `CONFIG_JUMP_LABEL=y` — without it, `static_key_enable` is inlined as a simple atomic operation that doesn't call `cpus_read_lock()`, so no deadlock occurs. Enabling `CONFIG_JUMP_LABEL` causes objtool build failures on the 5.8-rc6 kernel with the current toolchain. Updated TODO.md (attempt 2) and pushed.


